# DOM

The HTML DOM is a standard for how to get, change, add, or delete HTML elements.

* Document Object Model
* Tree of Nodes/Elements created by the browser
* Javascript can be used to read/write/manipulate to the DOM
* Object Oriented Representation

## DOM Programming Interface


`method` is an action you can do (add, deleting, finding an HTML element).

 `property` is a value that you can get or set (like changing the content of an HTML element).

```js
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "Hello World!";
```
In the example above, `getElementById` is a *method*, while `innerHTML` is a *property*.


## DOM Table


![](image-kw2kzeyo.png)


## Examine The Document Object

```js
// Get Document Properties
console.dir(document);
```
```js
// Get Document Domain Property

console.log(document.domain);
console.log(document.URL);
console.log(document.title);
console.log(document.domain);
console.log(document.domain);
```


## Get Element by ID

```js
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "Hello World!";
```


## Get Element by Class
>Requires index selection

```js
document.getElementsByClassName("test")[0].style.color = "green";
```

## Get Element by Tag Name



## Query Selector (Single Item)
```js
// Select ID, Class, or Tag

document.querySelector('#main-header');

```


## Query Selector All (Multiple Item)
```js
// Select ID, Class, or Tag

document.querySelectorAll('#main-header');

```
